Google App Engine SDK
<a href="http://code.google.com/appengine">Google App Engine</a> - that enables you to build web applications on the same scalable systems that power Google applications is out! Yes, there's Python involved and more to come. :-P<br /><br />I did some contributions to App Engine before its launch and wrote an article about how to index your data using the <a href="http://code.google.com/appengine/articles/bulkload.html">bulk uploader</a> in parallel. Yes, there's a really small search engine involved (ranking is up to you yet!).<br /><br /><a href="http://code.google.com/appengine/downloads.html">Download the SDK</a> while it's hot. Don't forget to read <a href="http://code.google.com/appengine/docs/whatisgoogleappengine.html">what the fuzz is about</a> before you jump on conclusions.
