get.Debian.net
I've a Toy Story to tell you today and to make a long story a short one: debian-br is proud to announce the birth of a new baby during debconf 7, smile and say hello world to: <a href="http://get.debian.net/">get.Debian.net</a><br /><br />If you don't want to figure out by yourself which one of the hundreds images (ISOs) available is the best for you to install Debian GNU/Linux. We do our best with get.Debian.net to figure out that automagically. You just need to use one of these javascript enabled browsers - yeah, nothing is perfect.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold;">What it does?</span><br /><ul><li>List the best images available to your architecture based on your browser information</li><li>List Win32 loader for those browsing the web site using Windows</li><li>get.Debian.net/bittorrent gives you link for torrents</li><li>Make Debian looks more sexy. Good enough, Sam? :-P</li></ul><br /><span style="font-weight: bold;">TODO</span><br /><ul><li>Use GeoIP for mirror selection - code in place, need list of mirrors</li><li>i18n support</li><li>List Live CD image where possible (i386 only?)</li><li>Add get.Debian.net/kde, /xfce and /gnome support</li><li>Figure out how to include usb and other images on the 1-click soup</li></ul><br />Download Debian: <a href="http://get.debian.net/">http://get.debian.net/</a><br />Download Debian using Bittorrent: <a href="http://get.debian.net/bittorrent/">http://get.debian.net/bittorrent</a><br /><br />Special thanks to faw and valessio.
