debcamp updates - round III
<ul><li>simple-cdd: During lunch Vagrant agreed we need a symlink from simple-cdd to build-simple-cdd, I've added it into my branch with some other minor changes and we will include that stuff in our next upload.</li><li>simple-cdd: After dinner Enrico told Vagrant about a simple-cdd demonstration and I said we could demo a 'merge' of both desktop and gnome-desktop tasks in a simple-cdd image containing just this new desktop profile, shrinking intentionally the list of packages. I'm sure people will be impressed how easy it's; the bonus point is learn more about the underrated tasksel. Stay tuned! :-)</li><li>d-i-g: I've a new branch just for the mirroring support, Otavio and I figured out that dp-m lacks proper multiple architecture support but I'll keep working on mirroring support on the 'dp-m' branch while I solve other problems and add new features on master and help Otavio add multiple arch support into dp-m. Lots of work. Python volunteers are welcome. git repository is at: git clone http://people.debian.org/~stratus/git/d-i-g.git</li><li>pkg-ltsp @ debian: You can say we've reunited here, me, vagrantc, otavio and pere. Vagrant is installing one Ltsp server and since we're short in time today - venue closing @ 11pm, probably we will have a lot more fun tomorrow.<br /></li><li>git and stgit: I'm in love with both tools, I blame Otavio that introduced me to them.</li><li>people: Tomorrow I and faw will be changing room and in a few days all the brazilian people will be reunited here. I can't wait to see the canteen really crowded with us and the rest of the Debian people attending debconf. See you all and have a nice trip!</li></ul>There's a lot more bits but I can't remember everything, oh I've also met siretart. :-)
